[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26428516","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-26428516","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":26428516,"user":{"login":"deepdiver1975","id":1005065,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67e101ad9531b7d25697b76e503e062e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975","html_url":"https://github.com/deepdiver1975","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-16t15:29:26z","updated_at":"2013-10-16t15:29:26z","body":"> disk quota set for the user.\r\n\r\nthe user in this context would be the user running the web server - i question the need for this.\r\nfrom my understanding the php function disk_free_space should respect the quota hp.net/manual/en/function.disk-free-space.php"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26484505","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-26484505","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":26484505,"user":{"login":"novij","id":111357,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/0dbda31729a954bd93ff7c9c2c9b34fe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f70e02d9f4e6666e38e3639a622c4bef9.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"0dbda31729a954bd93ff7c9c2c9b34fe","url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij","html_url":"https://github.com/novij","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/novij/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-17t07:38:47z","updated_at":"2013-10-17t07:38:47z","body":"in most setups it is state of the art to run php with the same uid as the user login. this is done by running php through cgi/fcgi, suexec, apache mpm itk or apache mpm peruser. the simpliest way to get such a setup is by using ispconfig.\r\n\r\nthe php function disk_free_space ignores quota limits, i've checked that on my setup.\r\n\r\nif you setup owncloud for a client with a quota of 5gb and he has already filled this up owncloud still tells him, he has hundreds of gb (free disk size) of free space. this lead to confusion of the customers."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26490261","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-26490261","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":26490261,"user":{"login":"deepdiver1975","id":1005065,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67e101ad9531b7d25697b76e503e062e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975","html_url":"https://github.com/deepdiver1975","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-17t09:29:11z","updated_at":"2013-10-17t09:29:11z","body":"> in most setups it is state of the art to run php with the same uid as the user login. \r\n\r\nreally - this is the first time i hear that - nevertheless in such a scenario your request makes sense.\r\n\r\ni really wonder how file sharing will work in such a setup - is owncloud working at all?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26490585","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-26490585","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":26490585,"user":{"login":"realrancor","id":2248459,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/f6105e79dfcfb0fcbabb3db061135c08?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f7a70061016eba74d85c060de0f65212d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"f6105e79dfcfb0fcbabb3db061135c08","url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor","html_url":"https://github.com/realrancor","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/realrancor/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-17t09:34:45z","updated_at":"2013-10-17t09:34:45z","body":"hi,\r\n\r\ncreating a feature request at the php bugtracker to add an function to the disk_free_space() method to respect the filesystem quota is probably a better idea. supporting all available quota systems on each operating system is probably a little bit overkill for an implementation in owncloud or am i wrong?"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26662969","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-26662969","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":26662969,"user":{"login":"bantu","id":189375,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fcdc48f189c0e2e8a870f3d54615a2f0d.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"88483d87947219efecfc570465c753b2","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu","html_url":"https://github.com/bantu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bantu/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-20t01:46:00z","updated_at":"2013-10-20t01:47:34z","body":"> in most setups it is state of the art to run php with the same uid as the user login. this is done by running php through cgi/fcgi, suexec, apache mpm itk or apache mpm peruser. the simpliest way to get such a setup is by using ispconfig.\r\n\r\nyes, shared hosting setups usually work like that. but then again, shared hosting setup usually also disallow the use of exec() and friends for security reasons. so the usefulness of your suggestion is questionable.\r\n\r\n> if you setup owncloud for a client with a quota of 5gb and he has already filled this up owncloud still tells him, he has hundreds of gb (free disk size) of free space. this lead to confusion of the customers.\r\n\r\nhosting providers need to tell their customers that there is a quota involved and that filesystem functions such as disk_free_space do not consider these quotas. then owncloud administrators should be able to just set the owncloud quota close to their filesystem quota. maybe this should be added to the owncloud documentation, not sure."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/29086741","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/5352#issuecomment-29086741","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/5352","id":29086741,"user":{"login":"philippfs","id":2259821,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e6c395cea8ba3962c9662ea98b5905ca?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f2b25c148896d7dc5660ba698f7b7a455.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e6c395cea8ba3962c9662ea98b5905ca","url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs","html_url":"https://github.com/philippfs","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/philippfs/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-11-22t16:31:48z","updated_at":"2013-11-22t16:31:48z","body":"well, 1and1 for example has this problem on its shared hosting and the use of exec() is allowed. so it would be great to add this to the core."}]